          "",
          "Logan Boese"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were a police detective in early twentieth century New York City, but had to retire from the force due to an injury in the leg. (A Gangster with a tommy gun took hostages, and gunned down several other officers before you were able to take him down. You were awarded a medal for it, and got a nifty nickname, \"The Silver Shinbone,\" but you never considered it a fair trade.) A lifelong officer, however, you had nothing better to fill your days with than booze, and, not wanting to be a drunkard like your father, you decided to go into work for yourself and became something of a local hero. Problem the police couldn't help with? Go see Cohen. Missing Child? Better get Cohen. Someone threatening you? Cohen can help. You did well for yourself, and were happy enough. You helped people and made money. Win Win. At least, until one case lead you after a missing sister, and straight into the world of the Kindred. Long Story Short, you got the girl back to your family, but traded your life. If not for the \"Young Turk\" of a Brujah, \"Fierce\" McPherson, you would have died. They gave you the embrace because you'd impressed them. After all, Regardless of your bum leg and mortal frame, you didn't hesitate for one minute after realizing that Vampires were real, and you just dove in and did your job. Ever since then, you've been doing basically the same job you did before, but now, some of your clients are dead. And, every so often, you have to relocate. Either because you're drawing too much attention, or because the local princedom has decided that there's a few too many Thin Bloods around, and you thought it best to make yourself scarce."
        ],
